WILLIAM C. DE MILLE PRODUCTIONS, Inc., Petitioner and Cross-Respondent, v. COMMISSIONER OF INTERNAL REVENUE, Respondent and Cross-Petitioner. No. 8083. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Jan. 7, 1936. ' Frank J. Wideman, Asst. Atty. Gen., and Robert H. Jackson, Asst. Gen. Counsel, Bureau of Internal Revenue, of Washington, D. C., for commissioner.

Before WILBUR, GARRECHT, and DENMAN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

On stipulation of counsel for respective parties, ordered, petitions to review herein dismissed; mandate forthwith.
